        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Requested sensitivity: 
As detailed in the Scientific Justification, we estimate the need of a sensitivity of ~40 mJy rms. With the dual polarization CO line and continnuum setup (see below), the sensitivity calculator estimates a total of ?17 min on source. With only one pointing needed the OT computes that this sensitivity can be reached in ~1 hrs execution time.

Imaging requirements: 
We require the highest available angular resolution available (0.1" in Band 9) for which we need a single array configuration. 


Correlator setup: 
We selected the correlator configuration that offers the maximum continuum sensitivity (dual polarization, ~6.09 GHz of aggregated bandwidth per polarization). We selected the ~1 km/s spectral resolution option at the observing frequency. This setup will allow us to detect CO(6-5) emission from the gas in the disc.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
